      </AttributeDefinition>

      </AttributeDefinition>

#Menu Labels menuLabel_connectionSetting=Connection Settings menuLabel_aggregationSetting=Aggregation Settings #Section Labels sectionLabel_gatewaySetting=Connector Gateway Settings sectionLabel_acf2Setting=ACF2 Connector Settings sectionLabel_aggregationSetting=Account Aggregation Settings # Section Info Labels sectionInfo_gatewaySetting=Each source must have a dedicated Connector Gateway. When configuring a source, the Host and Port entries of the Connector Gateway attributes are required. Enter the Host and Port of the machine where the Connector Gateway for the Mainframe System is installed.

Enable TLS for communication between the Virtual Appliance and Connector Gateway.

Enable Mutual TLS for communication between the Virtual Appliance and Connector Gateway. sectionInfo_acf2Setting=This section contains the information that the connector uses to connect and interact with the ACF2 System. Configure all the necessary parameters to successfully connect with ACF2 System.

Enter the Connector Name as configured in Mainframe connection configuration. It should be in uppercase.

Enter the Username that authenticates to the Mainframe System through the Mainframe Connector. sectionInfo_aggregationSetting=This section contains the information that the connector uses to aggregate Accounts.

A list of strings can be configured in Start Filter Condition for Accounts field. Connector aggregates all the accounts from Mainframe sources those start with any of the configured character sets. #docLink Labels docLinkLabel_connectionCredentials=Learn more about Connector Gateway settings docLinkLabel_acf2Setting=Learn more about ACF2 settings docLinkLabel_aggregationSetting=Learn more about Start Filter Condition for Accounts #PlaceHolder Labels placeHolder_MscsName=XXXACF2 #Helptext Labels helpKey_cGCertSubject=If subject of the certificate is not same as the FQDN of the Connector Gateway host, enter the CN value of subject of the certificate. helpKey_keystorePath=Keystore location at Virtual Appliance machine helpKey_keystorePassword=Keystore password for above specified Keystore helpKey_keyPassword=Key password for the private/secret key #Field Labels host=Host port=Port user=Username password=Password TLSEnabled=Enable TLS MscsName=Connector Name CGCertSubject=Certificate Subject disableHostnameVerification=Disable HostName Verification accountStartsWithFilter=Start Filter Condition for Accounts enablePE2TLSAuth=Enable Mutual TLS keystorePath=Keystore Path keystorePassword=Keystore Password keyPassword=Key Password #Short description ShortDesc=The integration provides capabilities to manage end-to-end CA ACF2 accounts and groups for deep governance with features such as data collection, accounts and permission assignment.

Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131, Ana kaynaklardan yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131lm\u0131\u015f herhangi bir karakter seti ile ba\u015flayan t\u00fcm hesaplar\u0131 toplar. docLinkLabel_connectionCredentials=Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 A\u011f Ge\u00e7idi ayarlar\u0131 hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin docLinkLabel_acf2Setting=ACF2 ayarlar\u0131 hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin docLinkLabel_aggregationSetting=Hesaplar i\u00e7in Ba\u015flama Filtre Ko\u015fulu hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin placeHolder_MscsName=XXXACF2 helpKey_cGCertSubject=Sertifikan\u0131n konusu Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 A\u011f Ge\u00e7idi ana bilgisayar\u0131n\u0131n FQDN'si ile ayn\u0131 de\u011filse, sertifika konusunun CN de\u011ferini girin. helpKey_keystorePath=Sanal Gere\u00e7 makinesindeki Keystore konumu helpKey_keystorePassword=Yukar\u0131da belirtilen Keystore i\u00e7in Keystore parolas\u0131 helpKey_keyPassword=\u00d6zel/gizli anahtar i\u00e7in anahtar parolas\u0131 host=Ana Bilgisayar port=Ba\u011flant\u0131 Noktas\u0131 user=Kullan\u0131c\u0131 ad\u0131 password=\u015eifre TLSEnabled=TLS'yi Etkinle\u015ftir MscsName=Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 Ad\u0131 CGCertSubject=Sertifika Konusu disableHostnameVerification=Ana Bilgisayar Ad\u0131 Do\u011frulamas\u0131n\u0131 Devre D\u0131\u015f\u0131 B\u0131rak accountStartsWithFilter=Hesaplar i\u00e7in Ba\u015flama Filtre Ko\u015fulu enablePE2TLSAuth=Kar\u015f\u0131l\u0131kl\u0131 TLS'yi Etkinle\u015ftir keystorePath=Keystore Yolu keystorePassword=Keystore Parolas\u0131 keyPassword=Anahtar Parolas\u0131 ShortDesc=Entegrasyon, veri toplama ve hesap ve izin atamas\u0131 gibi \u00f6zelliklerle derin y\u00f6netim i\u00e7in u\u00e7tan uca CA ACF2 hesaplar\u0131n\u0131 ve gruplar\u0131n\u0131 y\u00f6netme becerileri sa\u011flar.

<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Application PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Application caseInsensitive="true" connector="sailpoint.connector.sm.SMConnector" featuresString="PROVISIONING, SYNC_PROVISIONING, SEARCH, UNSTRUCTURED_TARGETS, ENABLE, PASSWORD, UNLOCK" icon="mainframeIcon" name="ACF2" type="ACF2 - Full">
  <Attributes>
    <Map>
      <entry key="IBMcharacterSet" value="IBM1047"/>
      <entry key="MscsType" value="ACF2"/>
      <entry key="TLSEnabled">
        <value>
          <Boolean></Boolean>
        </value>
      </entry>
      <entry key="appTemplateData" value="{ 'whiteListedAttributes': ['IBMcharacterSet','MscsType','TLSEnabled','beforeProvisioningRule','afterProvisioningRule','cloudCacheUpdate','cloudDisplayName','cloudExternalId','connectionType','connectorName','deleteThresholdPercentage','descriptionAttribute','disableHostnameVerification','disableHotpathForUpdate','enablePE2TLSAuth','encrypted','fieldDelimiter','formPath','healthy','listDelimiter','managementWorkgroup','since','sourceDescription','splAccountAttributes','splConnectionAttributes','status','templateApplication'] }"/>

  <Schemas>
    <Schema displayAttribute="USER_ID" groupAttribute="groups" identityAttribute="USER_ID" nativeObjectType="account" objectType="account">
      <AttributeDefinition name="USER_ID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>ACF2 ID of the user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition entitlement="true" managed="true" multi="true" name="groups" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>List of groups this user belongs to</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.ASSIZE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max address space size - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.CPUTIME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max cputime for a dubbed process - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.FILEPROC" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max files per process - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.HOME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>defines the pathname of the initial directory</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.MMAPAREA" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max-data-space pages-for-HFS-mappings - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.OMVSPGM" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>OMVS shell program started when the OMVS command is entered</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.PROCUSER" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max number of processes - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.THREADS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max number of pthread created threads - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.UID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User identification - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPIDENT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator ID - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPPRTY" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator priority - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.TIMEOUT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Idle time value - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.FORCE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Indicates whether the user is signed off (FORCE) or not signed off (NOFORCE) when an XRF takeover occurs. - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPCLASS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator class values - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="DCE.HOMEUUID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Home cell UUID - DCE user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="REVOKE_TYPE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Revoke type (SUSPEND, CANCEL, Both) of the user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="NAME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Name of the user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="UID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>UID pseudo field, concatenation of selected logonid fields</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition multi="true" name="UIDX" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Multiple values UID</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="SEC_VIO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Number of cumulative security violations for a user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="EXPIRE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>When the privileges for this logonid will expire</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="SECURITY" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User is a security administrator</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACCOUNT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can insert, list, change, and delete logonid records</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="LEADER" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display and alter certain fields of logonid records for other users.</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="AUDIT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display the records and parameters of the CA ACF2 system.</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CONSULT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display other logonid records</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="REFRESH" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can issue the /F ACF2,REFRESH operator command to update GSO</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="READALL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User has read and execute access to all data sets at the site</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can log on to TSO</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="STC" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Logonid is for use by started tasks only</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can sign on to CICS</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="IMS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>user can sign on to IMS</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="MAINT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>A logonid can access data sets without CA ACF2 rule validation or loggings by means of a specified program executed from a specified library</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="NON_CNCL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>A user with the NON-CNCL privilege defined in their logonid record has full access to any data set or resource despite any security violations that can occur during the access attempt</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACC_DATE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>The date of the last system access by this user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACC_TIME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Time of the last system access by this user (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_EXP" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Password has been manually expired</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_TOD" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Date and time when a password was last changed</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_DAT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Date of the last invalid password or password phrase attempt (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_TIM" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>last time a user entered an invalid password (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_VIO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>umber of password violations that occurred on PSWD_DAT</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOACCT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO logon account</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOCMDS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>TSO command list module name that contains the list of commands that this user is authorized to use</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOFSCRN" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can use the full-screen logon display</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOPERF" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO performance group</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSORBA" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Mail Index Record Pointer (MIRP) for this user</Description>

        <Description>Default TSO region size in kilobytes</Description>

      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOSIZE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Maximum TSO region size</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOTIME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO time parameter, which is the CPU time limit (in minutes) associated with the TSO session</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOUNIT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO unit name</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOPROC" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO procedure name</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="JCL" required="true" type="string">

      <AttributeDefinition name="ACF2CICS" required="true" type="string">

      <AttributeDefinition name="CICSCL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>CICS operator class</Description>

      <AttributeDefinition name="CICSID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>CICS operator ID</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICSPRI" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>CICS operator priority</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICSRSL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>CICS resource access key</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_MIX" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Current password is case-sensitive</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="NOMAXVIO" required="true" type="string">

    <Schema displayAttribute="GROUP_ID" identityAttribute="GROUP_ID" nativeObjectType="group" objectType="group">

        <Description>UID mask which defines this Group. (All users matching this UID mask belong to this group)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
    </Schema>

This file is generated by "sailpointTranslate" command. menuLabel_connectionSetting=Verbindungseinstellungen menuLabel_aggregationSetting=Aggregationseinstellungen sectionLabel_gatewaySetting=Anschluss-Gateway-Einstellungen sectionLabel_acf2Setting=ACF2-Anschluss-Einstellungen sectionLabel_aggregationSetting=Einstellungen f\u00fcr Kontoaggregation sectionInfo_gatewaySetting=Jede Quelle muss \u00fcber ein dediziertes Anschluss-Gateway verf\u00fcgen. Beim Konfigurieren einer Quelle sind die Host- und Port-Eintr\u00e4ge der Anschluss-Gateway-Attribute erforderlich. Geben Sie den Host und Port des Computers ein, auf dem das Anschluss-Gateway f\u00fcr das Mainframe-System installiert ist.

Aktivieren Sie TLS f\u00fcr die Kommunikation zwischen dem virtuellen Ger\u00e4t und dem Anschluss-Gateway.

Aktivieren Sie gegenseitiges TLS f\u00fcr die Kommunikation zwischen dem virtuellen Ger\u00e4t und dem Anschluss-Gateway. sectionInfo_acf2Setting=Dieser Abschnitt enth\u00e4lt die Informationen, die der Anschluss verwendet, um sich mit dem ACF2-System zu verbinden und mit ihm zu interagieren. Konfigurieren Sie alle erforderlichen Parameter f\u00fcr eine erfolgreiche Verbindung mit dem ACF2-System.

Geben Sie den Anschluss-Namen wie in der Mainframe-Verbindungskonfiguration konfiguriert ein. Er sollte in Gro\u00dfbuchstaben geschrieben werden.

Ana ba\u011flant\u0131 yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131lmas\u0131nda yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131ld\u0131\u011f\u0131 gibi Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 Ad\u0131n\u0131 girin. B\u00fcy\u00fck harfle olmal\u0131d\u0131r.

Ana Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 yoluyla Ana Sisteme kimlik do\u011frulamas\u0131 yapan Kullan\u0131c\u0131 Ad\u0131n\u0131 girin. sectionInfo_aggregationSetting=Bu b\u00f6l\u00fcm, ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131n\u0131n Hesaplar\u0131 toplamak i\u00e7in kulland\u0131\u011f\u0131 bilgileri i\u00e7eriyor.

Bir dize listesi Hesaplar i\u00e7in Ba\u015flama Filtre Ko\u015fulu alan\u0131nda yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131labilir. Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131, Ana kaynaklardan yap\u0131land\u0131r\u0131lm\u0131\u015f herhangi bir karakter seti ile ba\u015flayan t\u00fcm hesaplar\u0131 toplar. docLinkLabel_connectionCredentials=Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 A\u011f Ge\u00e7idi ayarlar\u0131 hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin docLinkLabel_acf2Setting=ACF2 ayarlar\u0131 hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin docLinkLabel_aggregationSetting=Hesaplar i\u00e7in Ba\u015flama Filtre Ko\u015fulu hakk\u0131nda daha fazla bilgi edinin placeHolder_MscsName=XXXACF2 helpKey_cGCertSubject=Sertifikan\u0131n konusu Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 A\u011f Ge\u00e7idi ana bilgisayar\u0131n\u0131n FQDN'si ile ayn\u0131 de\u011filse, sertifika konusunun CN de\u011ferini girin. helpKey_keystorePath=Sanal Gere\u00e7 makinesindeki Keystore konumu helpKey_keystorePassword=Yukar\u0131da belirtilen Keystore i\u00e7in Keystore parolas\u0131 helpKey_keyPassword=\u00d6zel/gizli anahtar i\u00e7in anahtar parolas\u0131 host=Ana Bilgisayar port=Ba\u011flant\u0131 Noktas\u0131 user=Kullan\u0131c\u0131 ad\u0131 password=\u015eifre TLSEnabled=TLS'yi Etkinle\u015ftir MscsName=Ba\u011flay\u0131c\u0131 Ad\u0131 CGCertSubject=Sertifika Konusu disableHostnameVerification=Ana Bilgisayar Ad\u0131 Do\u011frulamas\u0131n\u0131 Devre D\u0131\u015f\u0131 B\u0131rak accountStartsWithFilter=Hesaplar i\u00e7in Ba\u015flama Filtre Ko\u015fulu enablePE2TLSAuth=Kar\u015f\u0131l\u0131kl\u0131 TLS'yi Etkinle\u015ftir keystorePath=Keystore Yolu keystorePassword=Keystore Parolas\u0131 keyPassword=Anahtar Parolas\u0131 ShortDesc=Entegrasyon, veri toplama ve hesap ve izin atamas\u0131 gibi \u00f6zelliklerle derin y\u00f6netim i\u00e7in u\u00e7tan uca CA ACF2 hesaplar\u0131n\u0131 ve gruplar\u0131n\u0131 y\u00f6netme becerileri sa\u011flar.

<!DOCTYPE Application PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">

  <Attributes>

      <entry key="TLSEnabled">

      <entry key="appTemplateData" value="{ 'whiteListedAttributes': ['IBMcharacterSet','MscsType','TLSEnabled','beforeProvisioningRule','afterProvisioningRule','cloudCacheUpdate','cloudDisplayName','cloudExternalId','connectionType','connectorName','deleteThresholdPercentage','descriptionAttribute','disableHostnameVerification','disableHotpathForUpdate','enablePE2TLSAuth','encrypted','fieldDelimiter','formPath','healthy','listDelimiter','managementWorkgroup','since','sourceDescription','splAccountAttributes','splConnectionAttributes','status','templateApplication'] }"/>

        <Description>List of groups this user belongs to</Description>

      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.ASSIZE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max address space size - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.CPUTIME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max cputime for a dubbed process - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.FILEPROC" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max files per process - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>defines the pathname of the initial directory</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.MMAPAREA" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max-data-space pages-for-HFS-mappings - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.OMVSPGM" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>OMVS shell program started when the OMVS command is entered</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.PROCUSER" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Max number of processes - OMVS user profile</Description>

        <Description>Max number of pthread created threads - OMVS user profile</Description>

      <AttributeDefinition name="OMVS.UID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User identification - OMVS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPIDENT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator ID - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPPRTY" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator priority - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.TIMEOUT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Idle time value - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.FORCE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Indicates whether the user is signed off (FORCE) or not signed off (NOFORCE) when an XRF takeover occurs. - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CICS.OPCLASS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Operator class values - CICS user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="DCE.HOMEUUID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Home cell UUID - DCE user profile</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="REVOKE_TYPE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Revoke type (SUSPEND, CANCEL, Both) of the user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="NAME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Name of the user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="UID" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>UID pseudo field, concatenation of selected logonid fields</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition multi="true" name="UIDX" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Multiple values UID</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="SEC_VIO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Number of cumulative security violations for a user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="EXPIRE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>When the privileges for this logonid will expire</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="SECURITY" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User is a security administrator</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACCOUNT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can insert, list, change, and delete logonid records</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="LEADER" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display and alter certain fields of logonid records for other users.</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="AUDIT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display the records and parameters of the CA ACF2 system.</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="CONSULT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can display other logonid records</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>User can issue the /F ACF2,REFRESH operator command to update GSO</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="READALL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User has read and execute access to all data sets at the site</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>User can log on to TSO</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>Logonid is for use by started tasks only</Description>

      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>user can sign on to IMS</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>A logonid can access data sets without CA ACF2 rule validation or loggings by means of a specified program executed from a specified library</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="NON_CNCL" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>A user with the NON-CNCL privilege defined in their logonid record has full access to any data set or resource despite any security violations that can occur during the access attempt</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACC_DATE" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>The date of the last system access by this user</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="ACC_TIME" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Time of the last system access by this user (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_EXP" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Password has been manually expired</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_TOD" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Date and time when a password was last changed</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_DAT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Date of the last invalid password or password phrase attempt (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_TIM" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>last time a user entered an invalid password (read only)</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_VIO" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>umber of password violations that occurred on PSWD_DAT</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOACCT" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO logon account</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOCMDS" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>TSO command list module name that contains the list of commands that this user is authorized to use</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>

        <Description>Default TSO unit name</Description>
      </AttributeDefinition>
      <AttributeDefinition name="TSOPROC" required="true" type="string">
        <Description>Default TSO procedure name</Description>

      <AttributeDefinition name="PSWD_MIX" required="true" type="string">

This file is generated by "sailpointTranslate" command. menuLabel_connectionSetting=Verbindungseinstellungen menuLabel_aggregationSetting=Aggregationseinstellungen sectionLabel_gatewaySetting=Anschluss-Gateway-Einstellungen sectionLabel_acf2Setting=ACF2-Anschluss-Einstellungen sectionLabel_aggregationSetting=Einstellungen f\u00fcr Kontoaggregation sectionInfo_gatewaySetting=Jede Quelle muss \u00fcber ein dediziertes Anschluss-Gateway verf\u00fcgen. Beim Konfigurieren einer Quelle sind die Host- und Port-Eintr\u00e4ge der Anschluss-Gateway-Attribute erforderlich. Geben Sie den Host und Port des Computers ein, auf dem das Anschluss-Gateway f\u00fcr das Mainframe-System installiert ist.

Aktivieren Sie TLS f\u00fcr die Kommunikation zwischen dem virtuellen Ger\u00e4t und dem Anschluss-Gateway.

Aktivieren Sie gegenseitiges TLS f\u00fcr die Kommunikation zwischen dem virtuellen Ger\u00e4t und dem Anschluss-Gateway. sectionInfo_acf2Setting=Dieser Abschnitt enth\u00e4lt die Informationen, die der Anschluss verwendet, um sich mit dem ACF2-System zu verbinden und mit ihm zu interagieren. Konfigurieren Sie alle erforderlichen Parameter f\u00fcr eine erfolgreiche Verbindung mit dem ACF2-System.
